 of Douglasdale39岁，母亲Agnes Munfrode34岁。她和Hervey de Keith至少有1个儿子。她去世于大约1187年享年77岁。"},"hr":{"about 1112–about 1187":"oko 1112.–oko 1187.","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185.","1135–1220":"1135.–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–preminula","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185.","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"oko 1125.","1135":"1135.","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"oko 1112.","about 1145":"oko 1145.","about 1187":"oko 1187.","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"cs":{"about 1112–about 1187":"okolo 1112–okolo 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Zesnulá","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"okolo 1125","1135":"1135","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"okolo 1112","about 1145":"okolo 1145","about 1187":"okolo 1187","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"da":{"about 1112–about 1187":"omkring 1112–omkring 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Afdød","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"omkring 1125","1135":"1135","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"omkring 1112","about 1145":"omkring 1145","about 1187":"omkring 1187","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Skotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Skotland"},"nl":{"about 1112–about 1187":"circa 1112–circa 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Overleden","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"circa 1125","1135":"1135","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"circa 1112","about 1145":"circa 1145","about 1187":"circa 1187","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Schotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Schotland"},"en":{"about 1112–about 1187":"about 1112–about 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Deceased","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"about 1125","1135":"1135","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"about 1112","about 1145":"about 1145","about 1187":"about 1187","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Douglas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places called from their situation on a river named with Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black’ + <i>glas</i> ‘stream’ (a derivative of <i>glas</i> ‘blue’). There are several localities in Scotland and Ireland so named, but the one from which the surname is derived in most if not all cases is Douglas in Lanarkshire 20 miles south of Glasgow, the original stronghold of the influential Douglas family and their retainers.","History: The family taking their name from Douglas in Lanarkshire were of Flemish origin. They rose to great prominence in the 14th and 15th centuries, controlling the earldoms of Douglas, Morton, and Angus, and later, Queensberry."],"variants":[{"name":"Douglass","meanings":["Scottish and English (Durham and Northumbria): variant of   Douglas  .","History: William Douglass, a physician recognized for his identification and description of an epidemic of scarlet fever, was born <i>c.</i> 1691 in Gifford, Haddington County, Scotland, and settled in Boston in 1718. The abolitionist, orator, and journalist Frederick Douglass assumed the name after escaping from slavery in 1838 and traveling to Massachusetts. Son of a white father and a slave with some Indian blood, he was born Frederick Augustus Washington Bailey <i>c.</i> 1817 in Tuckahoe, MD."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Dev ."],"variants":[{"name":"Deborah","meanings":["Biblical name (meaning ‘bee’ in Hebrew), borne by the nurse of Rebecca (Genesis 35:8) and by a woman judge and prophet (Judges 4–5) who led the Israelites to victory over the Canaanites. It has always been popular as a Jewish name. It was in use among Christians by the mid 16th century and was taken up by the Puritans in the 17th century, in part because the bee was a symbol of industriousness. Since then it has enjoyed enormous popularity, peaking in the 1960s. Among other famous bearers is the actress  Deborah Kerr  (  1921–2007 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret de Douglas was born about 1112, her father, Sir John Douglas of Douglasdale, was 39 and her mother, Agnes Munfrode, was 34. She had at least 1 son with Hervey de Keith. She died about 1187, at the age of 77."},"et":{"about 1112–about 1187":"umbes 1112–umbes 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Surnud","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","1135":"1135","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"umbes 1112","about 1145":"umbes 1145","about 1187":"umbes 1187","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1112–about 1187":"noin 1112–noin 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","1135":"1135","1079":"1079","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1101":"1101","about 1112":"noin 1112","about 1145":"noin 1145","about 1187":"noin 1187","1109":"1109","Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Keith-Marischal, Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1112–about 1187":"environ 1112–environ 1187","1101–1145":"1101–1145","1112–1187":"1112–1187","1120–1141":"1120–1141","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1120–1185":"1120–1185","1135–1220":"1135–1220","1075–1145":"1075–1145","1079–Female":"1079–Décédée","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1075":"1075","1196":"1196","1141":"1141","Abt 1125":"environ 1125","1135":"1135","107